[[File:PIA16189_fig1-Curiosity_Rover-Rock_Outcrops-Mars_and_Earth.jpg|thumb]]与地球上的[[卵石|河流砾岩]]的比较，表明溪流中“强劲”奔流的水流<ref name="NASA-20120927">{{cite web |last1=Brown |first1=Dwayne |last2=Cole |first2=Steve |last3=Webster |first3=Guy |last4=Agle |first4=D.C. |title=NASA Rover Finds Old Streambed On Martian Surface |url=http://www.nasa.gov/home/hqnews/2012/sep/HQ_12-338_Mars_Water_Stream.html |date=2012-09-27 |publisher=[[NASA|NASA]] |access-date=2021-10-01 |archive-date=2020-05-13 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200513091007/https://www.nasa.gov/home/hqnews/2012/sep/HQ_12-338_Mars_Water_Stream.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="NASA-20120927a">{{cite web |author=NASA |author-link=NASA |title=NASA's Curiosity Rover Finds Old Streambed on Mars – video (51:40) |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=fYo31XjoXOk |date=2012-09-27 |publisher=[[NASA|NASA]]television |access-date=2021-10-01 |archive-date=2018-09-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180927204202/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=fYo31XjoXOk |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="AP-20120927">{{cite news |last=Chang |first=Alicia |title=Mars rover Curiosity finds signs of ancient stream |url=http://apnews.excite.com/article/20120927/DA1IDOO00.html |date=2012-09-27 |agency=Associated Press |accessdate=2021-10-01 |archive-date=2016-06-16 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160616205338/http://apnews.excite.com/article/20120927/DA1IDOO00.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。]]

[[美国宇航局|美国宇航局]][[好奇号|好奇号]]探测车在任务执行初期，就在火星上发现了清晰的[[河流作用|河流]]沉积物。这些[[露头|露头]]中的卵石特性表明，以前河床上曾奔流着强劲的水流，水流深度达脚踝和腰部之间。这些岩石是从陨石坑壁向下的[[冲积扇|冲积扇]]底部发现的，而这一冲积扇系统是以前从轨道上所识别出的<ref name="NASA-20120927" /><ref name="NASA-20120927a" /><ref name="AP-20120927" />。

2012年10月，好奇号对[[火星土壤|火星土壤]]进行了首次[[X射线晶体学|X射线衍射分析]]。结果显示存在包括[[长石|长石]]、[[辉石|辉石]]和[[橄榄石|橄榄石]]等在内的多种矿物，并表明样品中的[[火星土壤|火星土壤]]与[[夏威夷火山国家公园|夏威夷火山]]风化[[玄武岩|玄武岩土壤]]相类似。所使用的样本由来自[[火星土壤#大气尘埃|全球沙尘暴]]的尘埃和当地细砂组成。截止目前，好奇号分析的材料与对[[盖尔撞击坑|盖尔撞击坑]]中沉积物的最初看法相一致，这些沉积物记录了从潮湿到干燥环境期的变迁过程<ref name="NASA-20121030">{{cite web |last=Brown |first=Dwayne |title=NASA Rover's First Soil Studies Help Fingerprint Martian Minerals |url=http://www.nasa.gov/home/hqnews/2012/oct/HQ_12-383_Curiosity_CheMin.html |date=2012-10-30 |publisher=[[NASA|NASA]] |access-date=2021-10-01 |archive-date=2016-06-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160603091908/http://www.nasa.gov/home/hqnews/2012/oct/HQ_12-383_Curiosity_CheMin.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

2012年12月，美国宇航局报告说好奇号进行了首次全面性的土壤分析，揭示了[[火星土壤|火星土壤]]中存在水分子、[[硫|硫]]和[[氯|氯]]<ref name="NASA-20121203">{{cite web |last1=Brown |first1=Dwayne |last2=Webster |first2=Guy |last3=Neal-Jones |first3=Nance |title=NASA Mars Rover Fully Analyzes First Martian Soil Samples |url=http://mars.jpl.nasa.gov/msl/news/whatsnew/index.cfm?FuseAction=ShowNews&NewsID=1399 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121205005911/http://mars.jpl.nasa.gov/msl/news/whatsnew/index.cfm?FuseAction=ShowNews&NewsID=1399 |url-status=dead |archive-date=2012-12-05 |date=2012-12-03 |publisher=[[NASA|NASA]] }}</ref><ref name="NYT-20121203">{{cite web |last=Chang |first=Ken |title=Mars Rover Discovery Revealed |url=http://thelede.blogs.nytimes.com/2012/12/03/mars-rover-discovery-revealed |date=2012-12-03 |work=[[New_York_Times|New York Times]] |access-date=2021-10-01 |archive-date=2012-12-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121204075434/http://thelede.blogs.nytimes.com/2012/12/03/mars-rover-discovery-revealed/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。2013年3月，美国宇航局报告了矿物水合作用的证据，在多个岩石样本中，包括被碾破的“[[廷蒂纳岩石|廷蒂纳岩石]]”碎块和[[火星岩石列表#好奇号|“萨顿内露层”岩石]]，以及[[火星岩石列表#好奇号|“克诺尔”]]（Knorr）和[[火星岩石列表#好奇号|“韦内克”]]（Wernicke）等其他岩石的矿脉和结核中可能存在水合[[硫酸钙|硫酸钙]]<ref name="NASA-20130318">{{cite web |last1=Webster |first1=Guy |last2=Brown |first2=Dwayne |title=Curiosity Mars Rover Sees Trend In Water Presence |url=http://mars.jpl.nasa.gov/msl/news/whatsnew/index.cfm?FuseAction=ShowNews&NewsID=1446 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130322065943/http://mars.jpl.nasa.gov/msl/news/whatsnew/index.cfm?FuseAction=ShowNews&NewsID=1446 |url-status=dead |archive-date=2013-03-22 |date=2013-03-18 |work=[[NASA|NASA]]}}</ref><ref name="BBC-20130319">{{cite web |last=Rincon |first=Paul |title=Curiosity breaks rock to reveal dazzling white interior |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/science-environment-21340279 |date=2013-03-19 |publisher=BBC |access-date=2021-10-01 |archive-date=2021-03-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210308051408/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/science-environment-21340279 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="MSN-20130120">{{cite web |author=Staff |title=Red planet coughs up a white rock, and scientists freak out |url=http://now.msn.com/white-mars-rock-called-tintina-found-by-curiosity-rover |date=2013-03-20 |publisher=[[MSN|MSN]] |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130323164757/http://now.msn.com/white-mars-rock-called-tintina-found-by-curiosity-rover |archive-date=2013-03-23 }}</ref>。在探测车从[[布雷德伯里着陆场|布雷德伯里着陆场]]到[[格莱内尔格|格莱内尔格]]地的黄刀湾区穿越过程中，车载[[好奇号#动态中子返照率设备_(DAN)|动态中子返照率设备]]（DAN）所作的分析提供了地下水的证据，显示地下水含量高达4%，深度为60厘米（2.0英尺）左右<ref name="NASA-20130318" />。

2013年9月26日，美国宇航局科学家报告说，[[火星|火星]]好奇号探测车在[[盖尔撞击坑|盖尔撞击坑]][[伊奥利亚沼|埃俄利斯沼]][[石巢|石巢区]]的[[火星土壤|土壤样本]]中检测到大量化学结合态水（重量比1.5-3%）<ref name="ST-20130926">{{cite web |last=Lieberman |first=Josh |title=Mars Water Found: Curiosity Rover Uncovers 'Abundant, Easily Accessible' Water In Martian Soil |url=http://www.isciencetimes.com/articles/6131/20130926/mars-water-soil-nasa-curiosity-rover-martian.htm |date=2013-09-26 |work=iSciencetimes |access-date=2021-10-01 |archive-date=2017-06-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170623005252/http://www.isciencetimes.com/articles/6131/20130926/mars-water-soil-nasa-curiosity-rover-martian.htm |dead-url=yes }}</ref><ref name="Science-20130926a">{{cite journal |last=Leshin |first=L. A. |display-authors=etal |title=Volatile, Isotope, and Organic Analysis of Martian Fines with the Mars Curiosity Rover |date=2013-09-27 |journal=[[Science_(journal)|Science]] |volume=341 |issue=6153 |doi=10.1126/science.1238937 |pages=1238937 |pmid=24072926|bibcode=2013Sci...341E...3L |s2cid=206549244 |url=https://semanticscholar.org/paper/7f3089e0c3e10eb39e48ff007e04a778811683dd }}</ref><ref name="Science-20130926">{{cite journal |last=Grotzinger |first=John |title=Introduction To Special Issue: Analysis of Surface Materials by the Curiosity Mars Rover |date=2013-09-26 |journal=[[Science_(journal)|Science]] |volume=341 |issue=6153 |page=1475 |doi=10.1126/science.1244258|pmid=24072916 |bibcode=2013Sci...341.1475G |doi-access=free }}</ref><ref name="NASA-20130926a">{{cite web |last1=Neal-Jones |first1=Nancy |last2=Zubritsky |first2=Elizabeth |last3=Webster |first3=Guy |last4=Martialay |first4=Mary |title=Curiosity's SAM Instrument Finds Water and More in Surface Sample |url=http://www.nasa.gov/content/goddard/curiositys-sam-instrument-finds-water-and-more-in-surface-sample/ |date=2013-09-26 |work=[[NASA|NASA]] |access-date=2013-10-03 |archive-date=2019-05-02 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190502190744/https://www.nasa.gov/content/goddard/curiositys-sam-instrument-finds-water-and-more-in-surface-sample/ |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="NASA-20130926b">{{cite web |last1=Webster |first1=Guy |last2=Brown |first2=Dwayne |title=Science Gains From Diverse Landing Area of Curiosity |url=http://www.nasa.gov/mission_pages/msl/news/msl20130926.html |date=2013-09-26 |work=[[NASA|NASA]] |access-date=2013-10-03 |archive-date=2019-05-02 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190502194152/https://www.nasa.gov/mission_pages/msl/news/msl20130926.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="NYT-20131001">{{cite news |last=Chang |first=Kenneth |title=Hitting Pay Dirt on Mars |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2013/10/01/science/space/hitting-pay-dirt-on-mars.html |date=2013-10-01 |work=[[New_York_Times|New York Times]] |accessdate=2021-10-01 |archive-date=2019-05-02 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190502223705/https://www.nytimes.com/2013/10/01/science/space/hitting-pay-dirt-on-mars.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。此外，美国宇航局报告，探测车发现了两种主要的土壤类型：细粒[[铁镁质|铁镁质]]型和局部衍生的粗粒[[长英质|长英质]]型<ref name="Science-20130926" /><ref name="NASA-20130926b" /><ref name="Science-20130913b">{{cite journal |last=Meslin |first=P.-Y. |display-authors=etal |title=Soil Diversity and Hydration as Observed by ChemCam at Gale Crater, Mars |date=2013-09-26 |journal=[[Science_(journal)|Science]] |volume=341 |issue=6153 |doi=10.1126/science.1238670 |pages=1238670 |pmid=24072924|bibcode=2013Sci...341E...1M |s2cid=7418294 }}</ref>。铁镁质型与其他火星土壤及尘埃相类似，与土壤非晶态相的水合作用有关<ref name="Science-20130913b" />。另外，在好奇号探测车着陆点（以及时间更早更靠近极地的[[凤凰号火星探测器|凤凰号着陆器]]位置）都发现了可能使生命相关[[有机物质|有机分子]]检测变得困难的[[高氯酸盐|高氯酸盐]]，表明“这些盐类在全球范围内分布”<ref name="NYT-20131001" />。美国宇航局还报告，好奇号在前往[[格莱内尔格|格莱内尔格]]途中遇到的一块[[杰克·马蒂耶维奇|杰克·马蒂耶维奇]]岩石，是一种[[橄榄粗安岩|橄榄粗安岩]]，与地球上的非常相似<ref name="Science-20130926c">{{cite journal |last1=Stolper |first1=E.M. |last2=Baker |first2=M.B. |last3=Newcombe |first3=M.E. |last4=Schmidt |first4=M.E. |last5=Treiman |first5=A.H. |last6=Cousin |first6=A. |last7=Dyar |first7=M.D. |last8=Fisk |first8=M.R. |last9=Gellert |first9=R. |last10=King |first10=P.L. |last11=Leshin |first11=L. |last12=Maurice |first12=S. |last13=McLennan |first13=S.M. |last14=Minitti |first14=M.E. |last15=Perrett |first15=G. |last16=Rowland |first16=S. |last17=Sautter |first17=V. |last18=Wiens |first18=R.C. |last19=MSL ScienceTeam |title=The Petrochemistry of Jake_M: A Martian Mugearite |journal=[[Science_(journal)|Science]] |volume=341 |issue=6153 |doi=10.1126/science.1239463 |publisher=[[American_Association_for_the_Advancement_of_Science|AAAS]] |date=2013 |pages=1239463 |pmid=24072927 |bibcode=2013Sci...341E...4S |s2cid=16515295 |url=https://authors.library.caltech.edu/41547/13/Jake_M%20Stolper%20et%20al.%20%282013%29%20Science.pdf |access-date=2021-10-01 |archive-date=2021-08-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210811150621/https://authors.library.caltech.edu/41547/13/Jake_M%20Stolper%20et%20al.%20(2013)%20Science.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

2013年12月9日，美国宇航局报告，火星盖尔陨石坑内曾拥有过一座适宜微生物生存的大型[[湖泊|淡水湖]]<ref name="NYT-20131209" /><ref name="SCI-20131209" />。

2014年12月16日，又报告称[[火星大气层|火星大气层]]中的[[甲烷|甲烷]]含量出现异常的大幅起落；此外，好奇号探测车从岩石上钻取的粉末中检测到了有机化学物质。另外，根据氘氢比研究，发现火星盖尔撞击坑中大部分的水在古代即撞击坑湖床形成前就已流失，之后湖水继续大量流失<ref name="NASA-20141216-GW">{{cite web |last1=Webster |first1=Guy |last2=Neal-Jones |first2=Nancy |last3=Brown |first3=Dwayne |title=NASA Rover Finds Active and Ancient Organic Chemistry on Mars |url=http://www.jpl.nasa.gov/news/news.php?release=2014-432 |date=2014-12-16 |work=[[NASA|NASA]] |access-date=2014-12-16 |archive-date=2016-09-02 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160902032845/http://www.jpl.nasa.gov/news/news.php?release=2014-432 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="NYT-20141216-KC">{{cite news |last=Chang |first=Kenneth |title='A Great Moment': Rover Finds Clue That Mars May Harbor Life |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2014/12/17/science/a-new-clue-in-the-search-for-life-on-mars.html |date=2014-12-16 |work=[[New_York_Times|New York Times]] |access-date=2014-12-16 |archive-date=2019-04-10 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190410053339/https://www.nytimes.com/2014/12/17/science/a-new-clue-in-the-search-for-life-on-mars.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="SCI-20141216-PRM">{{cite journal |title=Mars Atmosphere – The imprint of atmospheric evolution in the D/H of Hesperian clay minerals on Mars |date=2014-12-16 |journal=[[Science_(journal)|Science]] |volume=347 |issue=6220 |pages=412–414 |doi=10.1126/science.1260291 |display-authors=1 |last1=Mahaffy |first1=P. R. |last2=Webster |first2=C. R. |last3=Stern |first3=J. C. |last4=Brunner |first4=A. E. |last5=Atreya |first5=S. K. |last6=Conrad |first6=P. G. |last7=Domagal-Goldman |first7=S. |last8=Eigenbrode |first8=J. L. |last9=Flesch |first9=G. J. |last10=Christensen |first10=L. E. |last11=Franz |first11=H. B. |last12=Freissinet |first12=C. |last13=Glavin |first13=D. P. |last14=Grotzinger |first14=J. P. |last15=Jones |first15=J. H. |last16=Leshin |first16=L. A. |last17=Malespin |first17=C. |last18=McAdam |first18=A. C. |last19=Ming |first19=D. W. |last20=Navarro-Gonzalez |first20=R. |last21=Niles |first21=P. B. |last22=Owen |first22=T. |last23=Pavlov |first23=A. A. |last24=Steele |first24=A. |last25=Trainer |first25=M. G. |last26=Williford |first26=K. H. |last27=Wray |first27=J. J. |bibcode=2015Sci...347..412M |pmid=25515119 |s2cid=37075396 |url=https://authors.library.caltech.edu/52528/7/Mahaffy-SM.pdf |access-date=2021-10-01 |archive-date=2021-08-31 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210831003453/https://authors.library.caltech.edu/52528/7/Mahaffy-SM.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

2015年4月13日，《[[自然_(期刊)|自然]]》杂志发表了一份好奇号所收集湿度和地面温度数据的分析报告，显示了火星夜间地表5厘米以下会形成液态卤水膜的证据，但水的活性和温度仍低于地球上所知微生物繁衍和[[代谢|代谢]]的要求<ref name="Torres 2015"/><ref>{{cite news |last=Rincon |first=Paul |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/science-environment-32287609 |title=Evidence of liquid water found on Mars |work=BBC News |date=2015-04-13 |access-date=2015-04-15 |archive-date=2021-11-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211127220608/https://www.bbc.com/news/science-environment-32287609 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

